			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is MC3 really worth 6aa?!<a name="24996"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 2 04 1:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It really boils down to how much worn Ft you have, or plan to have.
<br />

<br />
MC3 (total cost of 12 aa) will Quadruple your base Mana regen rate if you are wearing no FT gear.  However with each point of mana you get from gear, the AA's effectiveness is reduced, Changing it from 25% increase, to 20% etc, til you are getting 5% toatl increase at Base (1) + AA (4) + FT (15).
<br />

<br />
At 20 regen, you can Fade every 4.5 mins and maintain a decent mana pool in reserve.  Occasionally you may have to slap Fade twice though just to get all the mobs off you.
<br />

<br />
My personal goal is to get to 9 mana a tick regen.  (FT + MC =<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />  This will allow me to charm once a minute with ease, and never run out of mana.  
<br />

<br />
For bards our major Ft items are going to be Earing of the Solstice (FT1), Composers Boots (FT3), and Coldain Shawl (FT3).  Soltice is a great option for any bard for the fact that it can be done at any level, it effectively doubles your mana regen since it will most likely be your first piece of FT gear, and it is a good ear slot item in its own right.  The shawl is a bit more arduous, but can be soloed all the way up to shawl 7 (FT1), and only requires a small raid for the 8th.  This can also be gotten at any level.  Ornate boot molds are expensive, can only be crafted by players 55+ (or with flag), but are a great option also.  
<br />

<br />
Above and beyond those, a bard begins to have to compete for FT gear with the hybrids or go the LDoN route.  
<br />

<br />
I personally would be willing to sink the 17 aa's to get 4 additional mana regen, but i am looking at them as a set 4 aa's for 1 point isn't bad.  We just got a discount on MC1 is all.
<br />

<br />
Just my take on the situation from a purely mathematical view.</span></td>
