				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is MC3 really worth 6aa?!<a name="29653"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 23 04 10:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I lead raids 2 or 3 nights a week.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
That's clearly the key difference.  Means:
<br />

<br />
(A) You have less of an exp flow, and
<br />

<br />
(B) You have more need of the raid oriented AAs.
<br />

<br />
Less supply + more demand makes you more price sensitive than me.  Makes perfect sense to me.
<br />

<br />
I suppose all we can conclude is that this quesiton, like 90% of the rest, can only be answered with &quot;depends on your play style.&quot;
<br />

<br />
I'm tempted to make an EQDiva FAQ:
<br />

<br />
Q)  Should I get X AA ability?
<br />

<br />
A)  It depends on your play style.
<br />

<br />
Q)  Which is better, X weapon or Y weapon?
<br />

<br />
A)  It depends on your play style.
<br />

<br />
Q)  Which songs should I keep memmed?
<br />

<br />
A)  It depends on your play style.
<br />

<br />
Q)  Should I group with Shammies/Druids/Wizzies/Rogues etc?
<br />

<br />
A)  It depends on your play style.</span></td>
